    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6, then boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 7-9 min (10\u201312 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil a kettle</p><p>Remove a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> from the fridge to soften</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble and tear (or chop) your <strong>portobello</strong> and <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan</p><p>Cook for 6-7 min or until caramelised</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are caramelising, chop your <strong>parsley</strong>, including the stems, very finely</p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Carefully cut your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into 6-8 slices, without going all the way through the base</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Mix the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>butter</strong> with a<strong> </strong>drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl and add the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> garlic butter</strong></p><p>Grate your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>tin foil</strong></p><p>Spread the <strong>garlic butter</strong> between the slices of ciabatta then add the <strong>sliced ciabatta</strong> to the tray</p><p>Sprinkle with a 1/3 of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 5-6 min or until the cheese is starting to brown - this is your <strong>garlic bread</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the garlic bread is cooking, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the mushrooms have caramelised, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until reduced to a pasta sauce-like consistency</p><p>Stir through the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche </strong>and<strong> soy sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta</strong> to the sauce and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffled-mushroom-linguine-with-garlic-bread/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mushroom pasta</strong> in bowls with the <strong>garlic bread </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the pasta with the <strong>salad </strong>and <strong>truffle oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
